text: Sitting outside on Nov 4th in Cleveland, Ohio, it don't get much better than this!

Haven't tweeted in a long time, here's a quote, We take on the strength of that which we overcome.  So true!
Today is a beautiful day outside, the sun is shining and I can feel that spring is almost here, let's spend the day in appreciation!
Here is another really powerful message I read once:  We take on the strength of that which we overcome.  How true!
How many people out there are followers of Abraham throughJerry and Esther Hicks?

Until I have a following, I am going to leave words of wisdom every day:
Thoroughly to teach another is the best way to learn for yourself.
There are some days when I just feel really good, today is one of them.  Not worrying about tomorrow, just being in the moment!
You’ll never leave where you are, until you decide where you’d rather be.
I've heard Twitter mentioned here at work about 7 times today.  It's getting really popular.  It's happening!  I love that!
My newsworthy item of the day - Congratulations to Cesar Milan for his accomplishment in becoming a US citizen, he is an amazing person!
I am in San Francisco and I guess I am just a couple of blocks away from where Twitter's headquarters!
